		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				1)  I am not in favor of Alliances, but I won't whine if some people want to try it. <br>  <br> 2)  Yes, there can be a Good/Evil Alliance and it would not be an exploit.  In fact, if Neutral were to Dominate the server, Good and Evil might be forced to ally to defeat the larger threat, and once that is settled, go back to tearing each others throats out. <br>  <br> Once upon a time, the US and Iraq were allies against Iran.  Now we are enemies with Iraq.  Shit happens, politics and circumstances change. <br>  <br> It is only an 'exploit' if it is exploiting a loophole in the program.  Verant has released several statements which indicate that alliances of convenience or for RP are not verbotten.  Cross-Team Trading is legal, albeit risky for example. <br>  <br> But the code takes the bite out of an alliance in order to prevent exploits. <br>  <br> Consider this scenario:  A DE Cleric and a Troll Warrior are faced with a Good Human Cleric of Rodcet Nife and a Neutral Half-Elf Ranger of Karana.  If the Human and Half-Elf decide to put aside their differences to stand against Evil, they are STILL at a serious tactical disadvantage.  The Cleric can't buff or heal the Ranger, and the Ranger can not Buff the Cleric, or know how many HP or Mana he has remaining without resorting to /tells or somesuch. <br>  <br> If I were alone and jumped by Evil forces, I would not turn down aid from a Neutral.  Survival is paramount.
