			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				On a further note... <br>  <br> Historically, whenever there are 3 sides in ANY battle...it's ALWAYS 2 on 1.  Regardless of the reasons...that's the way it always is. <br>  <br> There WILL be alliances...written or unspoken.  Trust me on that one. <br>  <br> The only way that it wouldn't be 2 on 1 is if Evil attacked Good, Good attacked Neutral, and Neutral attacked Evil (or some such combination).  But take a look at that scenario..all 3 teams are both attacking and defending...making things difficult at best.  Alliances are made so that the two allies can concentrate on attacking, while the lone wolf has to defend. <br>  <br> As many have mentioned in previous posts, eventually the tide will turn, and the allies will switch.  Why is this a bad thing?  I think it sounds exciting.		

