				Acano, <br>  <br> I like your RP logic, but transpose Good and Neutral. <br>  <br> Look at the Good Alliance:  Rodcet Nife, the Prime Healer, basically a pacifist deity.  Quellious, the Tranquil, basically a pacifist deity.  The Marr Twins, Deities of Valor and Love, pretty touchy-feely shit there.  Tunare, the All-Mother. <br>  <br> GOOD is your 'weaker' faction in terms of using any means to get things done. <br>  <br> The Neutral Alliance:  Veeshan, Wurmqueen, Dragons are badass, nuff said.  Brell, the Duke of Below, he made Dwarves and Goblins, obviously he ain't a pussy.  Karana, Deity of Storms.  Bristlebane, Prince of Thieves, perhaps the truest example of Neutrality.  Prexus, the Oceanlord, the Kedge were no Pacifists, and we know the Deepwater Knights condone assassination.  Solusek Ro, the Deity of the Sun, concerned solely with personal power.  The Tribunal, who are judge jury and executioner. <br>  <br> From my perspective, Neutral and Evil are really the go-getter types, while Good is more introspective and passive.  At least from the Deity descriptions.
