			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				I don't see a conflict between a roleplay and PvP oriented approach to the game, even on Vallon Zek.  The class of people that abuse immortal healing to the point of an exploit generally coincide with the /ooc ranters, anti-PK zealots, and grief players.  The hardcore roleplayers and PvP enthusiasts tend towards the same camp, having essentially the same fun-oriented approach to the game. <br>  <br> I'll be roleplaying rabid evil this time around, but I anticipate scenarios where I will not KOS neuters, perhaps even goodies.  <br>  <br> The conflict will be with the lamers that try to abuse the mechanics for an advantage in PvP and because they are &quot;just leveling&quot;.  We need to nip that in the bud by being absolutely ruthless to anyone that abuses team protection to train, spout off /ooc, etc. <br> 
